@startuml Delete

actor User as "Users"
boundary "BlogDetailPage" as View #lightblue
participant ":reactionRoute" as Route #lightblue
control "authMiddleware" as Auth #Orange
control "reactionController" as Controller #lightblue
participant ":reactionService" as Service #lightblue
entity "reactionCommentModel" as Model #lightblue
database "MongoDB" as MongoDB #yellow

    User -> View: 1. Click reaction icon of yourself
    activate User
    activate View


    View -> Route: 2. DELETE /api/v1/reaction { reactionId }
    activate Route
    Route -> Auth: 3. authenticateUser(req, res, next)
    activate Auth
    ref over User, View, Route, Auth, Controller, Service, Model, MongoDB : 4. Middleware verifies access token

    Auth --> Route: 5. authentication success
    deactivate Auth

    Route -> Controller: 6. deleteReaction(req, res)
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Service: 7. deleteReaction(reactionId)
    activate Service

    Service -> Model: 9. deleteReaction(reactionId)
    activate Model

    Model -> MongoDB: 10. Delete existing reaction
    activate MongoDB
    MongoDB --> Model: 11. Return deleted reaction
    deactivate MongoDB

    Model --> Service: 12. Return result
    deactivate Model

    Service --> Controller: 13. Return deleted reaction
    deactivate Service

    Controller --> Route: 14. 200 OK + reaction
    deactivate Controller

    Route --> View: 15. Render deleted reaction
    deactivate Route

    View --> User: 16. Update the interface
    deactivate View
    deactivate User


@enduml